{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-d7fb674dfe8d", "date": "2026-07-10", "stream": "news", "headline": "Iran buries slain supreme leader Khamenei in Mashhad; successor Mojtaba stays hidden", "summary": "Iran interred Ayatollah Ali Khamenei at the Imam Reza shrine in Mashhad, closing a week of processions, while proclaimed successor Mojtaba Khamenei remains unseen.", "url": "https://www.timesofisrael.com/khamenei-buried-following-dayslong-funeral-procession-as-successor-remains-out-of-sight/", "source_domain": "timesofisrael.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["new source"], "topics": ["geopolitics", "world"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "Iran interred Ayatollah Ali Khamenei before dawn Friday at the Shrine of Imam Reza in Mashhad, the country's holiest site, closing a week of mass processions after the longtime leader was killed in the opening Israeli-US strikes of the war (28 February 2026). His son Mojtaba Khamenei — proclaimed successor by a clerical assembly in early March — has issued written statements but has not appeared in public since the war began, reportedly recovering from injuries sustained in the strike that killed his father. Crowds in Mashhad chanted threats against President Trump.", "why": "The choreographed funeral is meant to project continuity, but a supreme leader no one has seen leaves a visible succession question at the head of a state still in an active conflict.", "thread_id": "2026-07-03-news-khamenei-s-state-funeral-begins-in-tehran-with-1", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-03", "event_date": "2026-07-10", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "updated": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-10-news-iran-buries-slain-supreme-leader-khamenei-in-mas"], "editions": ["2026-07-10-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-d7fb674dfe8d", "edition": "2026-07-10-news", "fields": {"display_body": "Iran interred Ayatollah Ali Khamenei before dawn Friday at the Shrine of Imam Reza in Mashhad, the country's holiest site, closing a week of mass processions after the longtime leader was killed in the opening Israeli-US strikes of the war (28 February 2026). His son Mojtaba Khamenei — proclaimed successor by a clerical assembly in early March — has issued written statements but has not appeared in public since the war began, reportedly recovering from injuries sustained in the strike that killed his father. Crowds in Mashhad chanted threats against President Trump.", "why": "The choreographed funeral is meant to project continuity, but a supreme leader no one has seen leaves a visible succession question at the head of a state still in an active conflict.", "importance": 3, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-592cab3f8e9f", "date": "2026-07-10", "stream": "news", "headline": "SK Hynix raises $26.5bn in the largest US IPO ever by a foreign company", "summary": "South Korea's SK Hynix priced a Nasdaq listing at $149/share to raise $26.5bn, the biggest US IPO by a foreign firm, surpassing Alibaba.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/7/10/south-koreas-sk-hynix-raises-26-5bn-in-record-breaking-us-ipo", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["economy", "tech"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The South Korean memory-chip maker priced 177.9 million American depositary shares (ADS — US-traded certificates representing foreign shares) at $149 each for its Nasdaq debut, raising $26.5bn — beating Alibaba's $25bn 2014 listing as the biggest US IPO by a non-US firm, and second globally this year only to SpaceX's June debut. Unusually, the shares priced at a premium to the market rather than the customary discount, on demand for the high-bandwidth memory used in AI accelerators.", "why": "A Korean chipmaker choosing a US listing at record scale signals where investors think the AI-hardware money is, and deepens SK Hynix's tie to the US capital market.", "thread_id": "2026-07-10-news-sk-hynix-raises-26-5bn-in-the-largest-us-ipo-eve", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-10", "event_date": "2026-07-10", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "updated": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-10-news-sk-hynix-raises-26-5bn-in-the-largest-us-ipo-eve"], "editions": ["2026-07-10-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-592cab3f8e9f", "edition": "2026-07-10-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The South Korean memory-chip maker priced 177.9 million American depositary shares (ADS — US-traded certificates representing foreign shares) at $149 each for its Nasdaq debut, raising $26.5bn — beating Alibaba's $25bn 2014 listing as the biggest US IPO by a non-US firm, and second globally this year only to SpaceX's June debut. Unusually, the shares priced at a premium to the market rather than the customary discount, on demand for the high-bandwidth memory used in AI accelerators.", "why": "A Korean chipmaker choosing a US listing at record scale signals where investors think the AI-hardware money is, and deepens SK Hynix's tie to the US capital market.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-f6e5c1da7701", "date": "2026-07-10", "stream": "news", "headline": "Wildfire in southern Spain kills at least 11, with 19 missing", "summary": "A fast-moving wildfire near Los Gallardos in Almeria province, Andalusia, killed at least 11 people amid a heatwave, with 19 unaccounted for.", "url": "https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2026/07/10/12-people-killed-as-wilfires-tear-through-southern-spain", "source_domain": "euronews.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["new source"], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "A fast-moving blaze that broke out Thursday afternoon near Los Gallardos in Almeria province (Andalusia) and spread to Bedar has killed at least 11 people and burned ~3,150 hectares amid a severe heatwave; regional minister Antonio Sanz said 19 remain unaccounted for and that most or all of the dead appear to be foreign nationals — four were found in a right-hand-drive car suggesting British tourists. Authorities revised the toll up to 12 then down to 11. Witnesses said a fallen power line may have sparked it. It is the deadliest wildfire on record for the region.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-10-news-wildfire-in-southern-spain-kills-at-least-11-wit", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-10", "event_date": "2026-07-09", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "updated": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-10-news-wildfire-in-southern-spain-kills-at-least-11-wit"], "editions": ["2026-07-10-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-10T10:09:16Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-f6e5c1da7701", "edition": "2026-07-10-news", "fields": {"display_body": "A fast-moving blaze that broke out Thursday afternoon near Los Gallardos in Almeria province (Andalusia) and spread to Bedar has killed at least 11 people and burned ~3,150 hectares amid a severe heatwave; regional minister Antonio Sanz said 19 remain unaccounted for and that most or all of the dead appear to be foreign nationals — four were found in a right-hand-drive car suggesting British tourists. Authorities revised the toll up to 12 then down to 11. Witnesses said a fallen power line may have sparked it. It is the deadliest wildfire on record for the region.", "why": "", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
